utilMDE
Class ClassFileVersion

java.lang.Object
  utilMDE.ClassFileVersion

public class ClassFileVersion
extends java.lang.Object

Given a list of .class files, print the class file version and also the JDK/JRE version required to run it. A .jar file can also be supplied, in which case each .class file within it is procesed. Example use: java ClassFileVersion MyClass.class

Supplying the "-min JDKVER" argument suppresses output except for .class files that require at least that JDK version. For instance, to list all the .class/.jar files that require JDK 6 or later, in this or any subdirectory, run find . \( -name '*.class' -o -name '*.jar' \) -print | xargs java ClassFileVersion -min 6
